

# man_1_simple_shell
```man
.TH simple_shell 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter written in C
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.br
Run in interactive or non-interactive mode to execute UNIX commands.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
program is a lightweight implementation of a UNIX shell.
It reads user commands, parses them, and executes corresponding programs using
system calls such as
.B fork,
.B execve,
and
.B wait.

It supports both interactive (prompt) mode and non-interactive (pipe/file input) mode.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Display the current environment variables.

.SH FEATURES
- Executes external commands using PATH.
- Handles arguments.
- Handles End-Of-File (Ctrl+D).
- Provides error messages similar to /bin/sh.
- Supports both interactive and non-interactive execution.

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
main.c shell.c README.md
($) exit
.fi
.PP
Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
main.c shell.c README.md
.fi

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH AUTHORS
Fahad Abdulaziz Alghamdi <https://github.com/Fahad-9195>  
Nabel Nasser Aldwese <https://github.com/Nabelaldwese>

